## Limitations

The findings are based on available data and reports up to October 2023. The complexity of climate systems means that predictions about precipitation changes are subject to uncertainties. Regional variations and local climatic conditions can significantly influence outcomes, making it challenging to generalize findings globally. Additionally, the impact of human interventions and policy changes on climate patterns was not extensively covered in the sources reviewed.